> Risotto is so delicious, but the prospect of all that stirring can sometimes be a bit daunting. Chef Mimi to the rescue! She's simplified the process and created this recipe that can be baked in the oven - all the creamy, luxurious texture with none of the elbow work. If that wasn't enough, it also boasts the crowd-pleasing flavours of a margherita pizza!

== Risotto ==

Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C and fill and boil your #kettle{}. Halve, peel and chop the @Echalion shallot{1} into small pieces. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Pour the boiling @water{450%ml} into a #jug{} with the @vegetable stock paste{20%g}, stir well and set aside.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tbsp} in a large #ovenproof saucepan{} over medium-high heat and add the shallot @British smoked bacon lardons{90%g}.

> TIP: If you don't have an ovenproof pan, just cook in a normal saucepan then transfer to an ovenproof dish before the risotto goes in the oven.

Stir fry the bacon lardons until starting to brown, ~{2-3%minutes}. Add the shallot to the bacon, stir and cook until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}. Add the garlic and @tomato puree{30%g} and cook for ~{1%minute} more. Stir in the @risotto rice{175%g} and cook until it is slightly translucent, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Meanwhile, pour the stock into the rice then add the @baby plum tomatoes{125%g}(halved) and bring back to the boil. Cover with a #lid{} (or some tightly fitting foil).

> TIP: Transfer to an ovenproof dish, cover with a lid or foil at this point if your pan isn't ovenproof.

Pop on the top shelf of your oven and bake until the rice is cooked and the stock absorbed, ~{20-25%minutes}. Meanwhile, grate the @mature Cheddar cheese{60%g}.

== Pea Shoot Salad ==

While the risotto is cooking, halve the @lemon{1/2}(halved) and squeeze the juice into a large #bowl{}. Add the @honey{15%g} and whisk together with a #fork{}. Set aside.

== To Finish ==

When the risotto is cooked, remove it from your oven. Carefully take the lid off the pan and add a splash of water to loosen if you need to. Stir in a knob of @?butter{1%knob} (if you have some), the @sun-dried tomato paste{25%g}, Cheddar and the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g}. Stir together until combined. Taste and season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{} if you feel it needs it.

Add the @wild rocket{40%g} to your bowl of dressing and toss to coat. Serve the risotto in #bowls{} with the salad alongside. Enjoy!

> Step 2 MOD: If you've added bacon lardons to your recipe, add it to your saucepan before you add the shallot and stir fry until starting to brown, 2-3 mins. Add the shallot to the bacon and continue with the recipe as instructed. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling raw meat. Cook lardons thoroughly.